          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-10-12 12:47:57" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>pertaining to having been invited</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>invited</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>It is possible that this expression in {S:04002201400008} was a common popular saying, namely, an adage. There are certain problems in the understanding of this adage in {S:04002201400008}, for it would seem as though many persons are invited to do something, but few are permitted to do it. Perhaps this should be understood in the sense of ‘many are invited to apply, but few are selected.’ In this context, of course, both the invitation and the selection would be by God.</Comments>
